 AP900521-0063 AP-NR-05-21-90 0922EDT r a PM-TB-AIDS 05-21 0726 PM-TB-AIDS,0749 Increase Of Tuberculosis Due to AIDS Virus Poses New Health Threat By STEPHANIE SCHOROW Associated Press Writer BOSTON (AP) Tuberculosis is alarming health officials again because it's posing new health threats with its connection to the AIDS virus.
 Snider stressed that tuberculosis, unlike AIDS, is a curable disease and called for TB screenings at drug rehabilitation programs, prisons or other places where AIDS tests are being administered.
